I am disappointed to say the least. A friend and I ordered two dishes and were happy with one dish but didn't like the second dish of fish, my friend said it didn't taste right and asked for the waitress to take it back. Customarily they were supposed to offer to replace it with another dish or ask us what we would like to do, instead the owner brought "another" fish dish and told us the fish she serves is the best and there was nothing wrong with the food and so on. My friend offered to taste it and if we like it we will keep it, unsurprisingly the taste was the same. Instead of offering us another dish or act with any professionalism we were ignored for almost 30 minutes after that. There was attitude from the waitresses and open hostility. I mean we didn't come to a restaurant at this time especially, to be treated like we committed a crime!

Just added Sheger Cafe to my checklist of best Ethiopian cousins. Last week, we were exploring the fast-growing Ethiopian markets and dining options in Downtown Silver Spring and environs. We finally settled with Sheger after testing the other several restaurants in the area. In fact, my kids made me return to Sheger a couple of times. We loved specially their "quanta firfir" and "Veggie Combo."  Cozy place, good vibe, fabulous prices, good portion, consistent taste!  On one occasion, the waitress mistakenly overcharged us on our take-out order but we were later instantly refunded upon a quick phone call. Thank you Selam!
